CAPE TOWN – Telkom announced that it has launched new FreeMe prepaid bundles. The new FreeMe bundle package will form part of its new Summer promotion. The bundles include mobile data, WhatsApp data, SMSs, Telkom call minutes, and YouTube data. Telkom said the prepaid promotion will run from 20 September to 20 January 2019, and that terms and conditions apply. The subscriber said that 5GB, 10GB, and 20GB bundles receive up to “100+ hours” of free YouTube streaming, while the 20GB bundle also receives 1,500 call minutes to any network. An out-of-bundle rate of R0.30 per MB applies to all the bundles. However, the call minutes does exclude premium-rated numbers and the YouTube streaming allocation is valid for one week only. "Telkom FreeMe data bundles are for the makers of the beats, the fashionistas on the streets, the connoisseurs of the treats, and the voyagers in the heat. Plus, you get free WhatsApp, FREE Telkom-to-Telkom calls, free Messaging and now free YouTube", the company said in a promotional statement. Pricing .tg {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;} .tg td{font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;padding:10px 5px;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;overflow:hidden;word-break:normal;border-color:black;} .tg th{font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:normal;padding:10px 5px;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;overflow:hidden;word-break:normal;border-color:black;} .tg .tg-ohc4{background-color:#3166ff;color:#ffffff;text-align:center;vertical-align:top} .tg .tg-0lax{text-align:left;vertical-align:top} WATCH:    – BUSINESS REPORT ONLINE